# Project conventions (Claude reads this on session start)

## Stack
- Package manager: **pnpm** (never npm or yarn)
- Backend: fastify (not express)
- ORM: prisma
- Tests: vitest, located in `__tests__/` next to source
- Lint/format: biome (not eslint+prettier)

## Don't
- Don't import from `src/legacy/` — it's deprecated, slated for removal
- Don't add new ORM models without updating `prisma/schema.prisma` first
- Don't use default exports — named only
- Don't write comments unless the WHY is non-obvious

## Commands you'll need
- `pnpm dev`           start the API
- `pnpm test:watch`    re-run on save
- `pnpm db:migrate`    apply latest schema
- `pnpm lint`          biome check + format

## Where things live
- API routes: `src/api/<domain>/`
- Schemas (zod): `src/schema/`
- Background jobs: `src/jobs/`
- Tests: `src/**/__tests__/<file>.test.ts`
